    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BeginningOfMsgException, ConnectedCallExistsException, EndOfMsgException, IncorrectMsgStateException, InvalidActiveConnectionStateException, InvalidActiveDeviceStateException, InvalidCalledDeviceStateException, InvalidCallingDeviceStateException, InvalidCallToParkDeviceStateException, InvalidConnectionIDForActiveCallException, InvalidConnectionStateException, InvalidDestinationDeviceStateException, InvalidDeviceStateException, InvalidDivertingDeviceStateException, InvalidHeldConnectionStateException, InvalidHeldDeviceStateException, InvalidObjectStateException, InvalidParkToDeviceStateException, MsgSuspendedException, NoActiveCallException, NoCallToAnswerException, NoCallToClearException, NoCallToCompleteException, NoConnectionToClearException, NoHeldCallException, NotAbleToPlayException, NotAbleToResumeException

    public class StateIncompatibilityException
extends CstaException
    Signals that a CSTA StateIncompatibilityError has occurred. StateIncompatibilityErrors indicate an error in the service request. Applications can catch specific sub-exceptions and/or retrieve the specific CSTA error using the getStateIncompatibilityError method.
    Author:
    Avaya Inc.
    See Also:
    "ECMA-269, sections 9.3 Diagnostic Error Definitions and 12.2.14 ErrorValue", Serialized Form

      • StateIncompatibilityException

        public StateIncompatibilityException(java.lang.Throwable cause)
        Constructs a new exception with the specified cause and a detail message. The detail message typically contains the class and the cause in string form. If the specified cause is null, then the cause string in the detail message is also null. This constructor is useful for exceptions that are little more than wrappers for other throwables.
        Parameters:
        cause - the cause (which is saved for later retrieval by the Throwable.getCause() method). (A null value is permitted, and indicates that the cause is nonexistent or unknown.)

        Note that the detail message associated with cause is not automatically incorporated in this exception's detail message.

        cause - the cause (which is saved for later retrieval by the Throwable.getCause() method). A null value is permitted, and indicates that the cause is nonexistent or unknown.
